[26 U.S.C. § 61](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section61&num=0&edition=prelim) defines gross income; [§ 62](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section62&num=0&edition=prelim) lays out the above-the-line adjustments that turn gross income into Adjusted Gross Income (AGI). For [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 11a, the engine simply sums the components computed by the prior stages.

